This paper discusses the development of a Collaborative Intrusion Detection System (CIDS) for IoT networks using blockchain technology. The primary focus is on network security and intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the architecture and implementation of the system, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the system's effectiveness, which involves software engineering (cs.SE).
